Project 4: User Testing with Selenium IDE
Course: MSSE 640
Student: Anusha Reddy
Application Under Test: Online Boutique (Google Microservices Demo)
Testing Tool: Selenium IDE

1. Introduction
This project focuses on applying automated UI testing techniques using Selenium IDE. The goal is to validate core user interactions within the Online Boutique microservices application deployed locally at:
http://localhost:8080


The assignment required creating a series of automated tests that simulate real user behavior, verify expected outcomes, and document the results. Five test cases were developed to cover essential e‑commerce flows, including loading the homepage, viewing product details, adding items to the cart, clearing the cart, and accessing the checkout page.
All tests were recorded, executed, and validated using Selenium IDE.

2. Test Environment
Component                    Details
Browser                      Google Chrome
Testing Tool                 Selenium IDE
Application                  Online Boutique(local deployment)
Operating System             Windows

Developer Tools were used to inspect elements, identify selectors, and validate UI structure during test creation.

3. Test Plan (Given / When / Then Format)
TC01 – Homepage Loads
- Given the user opens the Online Boutique application
- When the homepage loads
- Then key UI elements should be visible
TC02 – View Product Details
- Given the user is on the homepage
- When they click a product
- Then the product detail page should display
TC03 – Add Item to Cart
- Given the user is viewing a product
- When they click Add to Cart
- Then the item should appear in the cart
TC04 – Clear Cart
- Given the user has items in the cart
- When they click Clear cart
- Then the cart should show “Your cart is empty”
TC05 – Checkout Page Loads
- Given the user has at least one item in the cart
- When they click Checkout
- Then the checkout form should load successfully

