6. Reflection
Completing this project strengthened my understanding of automated UI testing and the capabilities of Selenium IDE. Key takeaways include:
- How to record and refine Selenium IDE test flows
- How to use assertions to validate UI behavior
- How to inspect elements and identify reliable selectors
- How to troubleshoot failing steps and adjust test logic
- Understanding the Online Boutique UI structure, including the use of a Clear cart button instead of individual item removal
This project also reinforced the importance of repeatable, automated testing for validating user-facing functionality.

7. Conclusion
All five Selenium IDE test cases were successfully created, executed, and validated. The Online Boutique application behaved as expected across all major user flows, demonstrating stable functionality and predictable UI behavior.




